  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to investigate the impact of continuous renal
      replacement therapy and intermittent renal replacement therapy on microbubble / cerebral
      microemboli generation in a cohort of critically ill patients with dialysis-dependent acute
      kidney injury.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
